==English==

===Etymology===
From Latin ''plicare'', ''to fold'' + Greek ''tetra'', ''four''. <!-- similarily, homosexual is the Greek prefix ''homo-'' plus the Latin ''sexualitis''. -->

===Noun===
'''tetraplicate'''
# ''(Science)'': one of a set of four [[identical]] objects, experiments, or [[copies]].  See also [[quadruplicate]].

===Adjective===
'''tetraplicate'''
# ''(Science)'': in or of four [[identical]] [[experiment]]s.  See also [[quadruplicate]].



===Examples===
# ''(noun)'': ''All samples were analyzed in tetraplicate on separate TLC plates.'' [http://jasn.asnjournals.org/cgi/content/full/15/6/1495]
# ''(adjective)'': ''The results represent the mean [...] of tetraplicate experimental treatments (n = 4).'' [http://www.jbc.org/cgi/content/full/278/33/31177]